      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Focusing strictly on the original text is the cornerstone of originalist legal theory, which prioritizes what the words meant at the time of ratification. However, the challenge lies in defining \"original intent\"—do you mean the public meaning, the specific intent of Framers, or something else? The \"activism\" critique often arises when current rulings appear to push the boundaries of what historical scholarship suggests was understood, leading to the perception of judicial overreach.",
